title: Projects
text:
Project 1
For my data driven project for DACSS 602, I explored the use of social media habits of Americans. As technology continues to advance, the use of social media has become a popular form of communication and interaction among people of various ages worldwide the popularity of social media has seen a remarkable surge in usage since its inception our study explored whether the frequency and duration of social media use impact the mental health and well-being of adult population. Our research question was: does frequency and duration of social media use affect the mental health of well-being of adults?

title: About Me
text:
Thank you for visiting my website. This page was created for Assignment #4 for DACSS 604.
I am currently a graduate student in the Data Analytics and Computational Social Science Program, also known as DACSS, at the University of Massachusetts- Amherst. I received by Bachelor’s Degree in Psychology, with a minor in Anthropology, from Mount Holyoke College. For over a decade, I have been working for state agencies, and I am currently employed full-time as an employee for the Commonwealth of Massachusetts. My academic background has given me a foundation in understanding human behavior, which I am now complementing with data analytics skills to improve decision-making processes.
Thanks for checking out my web site!
